  <div id="hdb" class="scroll-mt-40">
    <DefBox
      term="Keeping a Miniature Schnauzer in an HDB flat"
      definition="The Miniature Schnauzer is named on the HDB-approved breed list, so you can keep one in an HDB flat. HDB allows one dog of an approved breed per flat, and the Mini Schnauzer sits comfortably inside the small-breed rules. Every Mini Schnauzer we place has its dog licensing completed at purchase, so the paperwork is handled for you."
      bridge="Is a Miniature Schnauzer HDB-approved? Yes, by name on the list, and it has been one of Singapore's most popular HDB breeds for decades. Just mind the one-dog-per-flat rule, and if you already have a dog, message us first so we can check your situation."
