              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[var(--color-coral-500)]" aria-hidden="true">
                <path d="M20 6 9 17l-5-5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
              </svg>
              {fact}
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </CaptionedBlock>

    <PawTrail bg="bg-[var(--color-surface)]" colorClass="text-[var(--color-coral-300)]" />
  </div>

  <CaptionedBlock heading="Your Mini Schnauzer's First Week at Home" imageAlt="Miniature Schnauzer puppy settling into a set-up playpen during its first week home" imageSrc={imgScene5} imagePosition="left">
    <p>Day 0: we deliver, free, at a time that suits you, usually morning or evening. The playpen, bed, water, and toys are set up before your Schnauzer explores the room, and we walk you through all 30+ starter-kit items in person. Learn more about <a href="/delivery/" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">how our free home delivery and setup works</a>.</p>
    <p>Days 1 to 3: keep it calm and predictable. A fixed feeding routine, the toilet pads where we placed them, and short, gentle play. Some night whimpering is normal adjustment, and this confident breed usually settles quickly.</p>
    <p>Days 4 to 7: the routine sticks, and the personality arrives on schedule. Book your free first lesson with an AVS-certified trainer this week; early manners are what separate a charming Schnauzer from a loud one. See <a href="/free-training/" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">what the free AVS-certified training lesson covers</a>. For anything in between, you WhatsApp us.</p>
  </CaptionedBlock>

